dbpProtocolErrorNotifEnabled.name: dbpProtocolErrorNotifEnabled
dbpProtocolErrorNotifEnabled.description: Setting the value of this object to True(1) enables the dbpProtocolErrorNotif notification.

dbpProtocolErrorNotif.name: dbpProtocolErrorNotif
dbpProtocolErrorNotif.description: An dbpProtocolError Notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of dbpProtocolErrorNotifEnabled is True(1) 2) the value of dbpPerPeerStatsProtocolErrors changes It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls. An agent must not generate more than one dbpProtocolError 'notification event' in a five second period, where a 'notification event' is the transmission of a single Notification PDU to a list of Notification destinations. If additional premanent failures occur within the five second 'throttling' period, then these notification events should be suppressed by the agent. An NMS should periodically check the value of dbpPerPeerStatsProtocolErrors to detect any missed dbpProtocolError notification events, e.g. due to throttling or transmission loss.

dbpTransientFailureNotifEnabled.name: dbpTransientFailureNotifEnabled
dbpTransientFailureNotifEnabled.description: Setting the value of this object to True(1) enables the dbpTransientFailure Notification.

dbpTransientFailureNotif.name: dbpTransientFailureNotif
dbpTransientFailureNotif.description: An dbpTransientFailure Notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of dbpTransientFailureNotifEnabled is True(1) 2) the value of dbpPerPeerStatsTransientFailures changes It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls. An agent must not generate more than one dbpTransientFailure 'notification event' in a five second period, where a 'notification event' is the transmission of a single notification PDU to a list of notification destinations. If additional transient failures occur within the five second 'throttling' period, then these notification events should be suppressed by the agent. An NMS should periodically check the value of dbpPerPeerStatsTransientFailures to detect any missed dbpTransientFailure notification events, e.g. due to throttling or transmission loss.

dbpPermanentFailureNotifEnabled.name: dbpPermanentFailureNotifEnabled
dbpPermanentFailureNotifEnabled.description: Setting the value of this object to True(1) enables the dbpPermanentFailure notification.

dbpPermanentFailureNotif.name: dbpPermanentFailureNotif
dbpPermanentFailureNotif.description: An dbpPermanentFailure notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of dbpPermanentFailureNotifEnabled is True(1) 2) the value of dbpPerPeerStatsPermanentFailures changes It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls. An agent must not generate more than one dbpPermanentFailure 'notification event' in a five second period, where a 'notification event' is the transmission of a single notification PDU to a list of notification destinations. If additional premanent failures occur within the five second 'throttling' period, then these trap-events should be suppressed by the agent. An NMS should periodically check the value of dbpPerPeerStatsPermanentFailures to detect any missed dbpPermanentFailure trap-events, e.g. due to throttling or transmission loss.

dbpPeerConnectionDownNotifEnabled.name: dbpPeerConnectionDownNotifEnabled
dbpPeerConnectionDownNotifEnabled.description: Setting the value of this object to True(1) enables the dbpPeerConnectionDown notification.

dbpPeerConnectionDownNotif.name: dbpPeerConnectionDownNotif
dbpPeerConnectionDownNotif.description: An dbpPeerConnectionDown notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of dbpPeerConnectionDownNotifEnabled is True(1) 2) dbpPerPeerStatsState changes to closed(1) It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls. An agent must not generate more than one dbpPeerConnectionDown 'notification event' in a five second period, where a 'notification event' is the transmission of a single notification PDU to a list of notification destinations. If additional 'transport down' events occur within the five second 'throttling' period, then these trap-events should be suppressed by the agent.

dbpPeerConnectionUpNotifEnabled.name: dbpPeerConnectionUpNotifEnabled
dbpPeerConnectionUpNotifEnabled.description: Setting the value of this object to True(1) enables the dbpPeerConnectionUp notification.

dbpPeerConnectionUpNotif.name: dbpPeerConnectionUpNotif
dbpPeerConnectionUpNotif.description: An dbpPeerConnectionUp notification is sent when both thefollowing conditions are true: 1) the value of dbpPeerConnectionUpNotifEnabled is True(1) 2) the value of dbpPerPeerStatsState changes to either rOpen(6)or iOpen(7) It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls. An agent must not generate more than one dbpPeerConnectionDown 'notification event' in a five second period, where a 'notification event' is the transmission of a single notification PDU to a list of notification destinations. If additional 'transport down' events occur within the five second 'throttling' period, then these trap-events should be suppressed by the agent.

dbpLocalId.name: dbpLocalId
dbpLocalId.description: The implementation-specific identification string for the Diameter software in use on the system; for example: 'diameterd'

dbpLocalIpAddrTable.name: dbpLocalIpAddrTable
dbpLocalIpAddrTable.description: The table listing the Diameter local host's IP Addresses.

dbpLocalIpAddrEntry.name: dbpLocalIpAddrEntry
dbpLocalIpAddrEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter local host IP Address.

dbpLocalIpAddrIndex.name: dbpLocalIpAddrIndex
dbpLocalIpAddrIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the number of IP Addresses supported by this Diameter host.

dbpLocalIpAddrType.name: dbpLocalIpAddrType
dbpLocalIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address stored in dbpLocalIpAddress.

dbpLocalIpAddress.name: dbpLocalIpAddress
dbpLocalIpAddress.description: The IP-Address of the host, which is of the type specified in dbpLocalIpAddrType.

dbpLocalOriginHost.name: dbpLocalOriginHost
dbpLocalOriginHost.description: This object represents the Local Origin Host.

dbpLocalRealm.name: dbpLocalRealm
dbpLocalRealm.description: This object represents the Local Realm Name.

dbpLocalStatsTotalMessagesIn.name: dbpLocalStatsTotalMessagesIn
dbpLocalStatsTotalMessagesIn.description: The total number of Diameter Base Protocol messages received.

dbpLocalStatsTotalMessagesOut.name: dbpLocalStatsTotalMessagesOut
dbpLocalStatsTotalMessagesOut.description: The total number of Diameter Base Protocol messages transmitted.

dbpLocalStatsTotalUpTime.name: dbpLocalStatsTotalUpTime
dbpLocalStatsTotalUpTime.description: This object represents the total time this Diameter server has been up until now.

dbpLocalResetTime.name: dbpLocalResetTime
dbpLocalResetTime.description: If the server keeps persistent state (e.g., a process) and supports a 'reset' operation (e.g., can be told to re-read configuration files), this value will be the time elapsed (in hundredths of a second) since the server was 'reset'. For software that does not have persistence or does not support a 'reset' operation, this value will be zero.

dbpLocalConfigReset.name: dbpLocalConfigReset
dbpLocalConfigReset.description: Status/action object to reinitialize any persistent server state. When set to reset(2), any persistent server state (such as a process) is reinitialized as if the server had just been started. This value will never be returned by a read operation. When read, one of the following values will be returned: other(1) - server in some unknown state; reset(2) - command to reinitialize server state; initializing(3) - server (re)initializing; running(4) - server currently running.

dbpLocalApplicationsTable.name: dbpLocalApplicationsTable
dbpLocalApplicationsTable.description: The table listing the Diameter applications supported by this server.

dbpLocalApplicationsEntry.name: dbpLocalApplicationsEntry
dbpLocalApplicationsEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter application on this server.

dbpLocalApplicationsIndex.name: dbpLocalApplicationsIndex
dbpLocalApplicationsIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying a supported Diameter application. Upon reload, dbpLocalApplIndex values may be changed.

dbpLocalApplStorageType.name: dbpLocalApplStorageType
dbpLocalApplStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the columnar objects is writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

dbpLocalApplicationsStatus.name: dbpLocalApplicationsStatus
dbpLocalApplicationsStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the cdsgStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding dbpLocalApplIndex has been set. dbpLocalApplIndex may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of dbpLocalApplStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with dbpLocalApplStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with dbpLocalApplStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

dbpPeerTable.name: dbpPeerTable
dbpPeerTable.description: The table listing information regarding the discovered or configured Diameter peer servers.

dbpPeerEntry.name: dbpPeerEntry
dbpPeerEntry.description: A row entry representing a discovered or configured Diameter peer server.

dbpPeerIndex.name: dbpPeerIndex
dbpPeerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each Diameter peer with which the host server communicates. Upon reload, dbpPeerIndex values may be changed.

dbpPeerId.name: dbpPeerId
dbpPeerId.description: The server identifier for the Diameter peer. It must be unique and non-empty.

dbpPeerPortConnect.name: dbpPeerPortConnect
dbpPeerPortConnect.description: The connection port this server used to connect to the Diameter peer. If there is no active connection, this value will be zero(0).

dbpPeerPortListen.name: dbpPeerPortListen
dbpPeerPortListen.description: The port the server is listening on.

dbpPeerProtocol.name: dbpPeerProtocol
dbpPeerProtocol.description: The transport protocol (tcp/sctp) the Diameter peer is using.

dbpPeerSecurity.name: dbpPeerSecurity
dbpPeerSecurity.description: The security the Diameter peer is using. other(1) - Unknown Security Protocol tls(2) - Transport Layer Security Protocol ipsec(3) - Internet Protocol Security

dbpPeerFirmwareRevision.name: dbpPeerFirmwareRevision
dbpPeerFirmwareRevision.description: Firmware revision of peer. If no firmware revision, the revision of the Diameter software module may be reported instead.

dbpPeerStorageType.name: dbpPeerStorageType
dbpPeerStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Only the dbpPeerPortListen object is writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

dbpPeerStatus.name: dbpPeerStatus
dbpPeerStatus.description: Status of the peer entry: creating the entry enables the peer, destroying the entry disables the peer.

dbpPeerIpAddrTable.name: dbpPeerIpAddrTable
dbpPeerIpAddrTable.description: The table listing the Diameter peer IP addresses.

dbpPeerIpAddrEntry.name: dbpPeerIpAddrEntry
dbpPeerIpAddrEntry.description: A row entry representing a peer Diameter server.

dbpPerrIpAddressIndex.name: dbpPerrIpAddressIndex
dbpPerrIpAddressIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the number of IP Addresses supported by all Diameter peers.

dbpPeerIpAddressType.name: dbpPeerIpAddressType
dbpPeerIpAddressType.description: The type of address stored in diameterPeerIpAddress.

dbpPeerIpAddress.name: dbpPeerIpAddress
dbpPeerIpAddress.description: The active IP Address(es) used for connections.

dbpAppAdvToPeerTable.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerTable
dbpAppAdvToPeerTable.description: The table listing the applications advertised by this host to each peer and the types of service supported: accounting, authentication or both.

dbpAppAdvToPeerEntry.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerEntry
dbpAppAdvToPeerEntry.description: A row entry representing a discovered or configured Diameter peer server.

dbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId
dbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId.description: The IANA Enterprise Code value assigned to the vendor of the Diameter device.

dbpAppAdvToPeerIndex.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerIndex
dbpAppAdvToPeerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying a Diameter application advertised as supported by this host to each peer. Upon reload, dbpAppAdvToPeerIndex values may be changed

dbpAppAdvToPeerServices.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerServices
dbpAppAdvToPeerServices.description: The type of services supported for each application, accounting, authentication or both.

dbpAppAdvToPeerStorageType.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerStorageType
dbpAppAdvToPeerStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the objects are writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

dbpAppAdvToPeerStatus.name: dbpAppAdvToPeerStatus
dbpAppAdvToPeerStatus.description: Status of the entry: creating the entry causes the application to be advertised, destroying the entry ceases advertisement.

dbpAppAdvFromPeerTable.name: dbpAppAdvFromPeerTable
dbpAppAdvFromPeerTable.description: The table listing the applications advertised by each peer to this host and the types of service supported: accounting, authentication or both.

dbpAppAdvFromPeerEntry.name: dbpAppAdvFromPeerEntry
dbpAppAdvFromPeerEntry.description: A row entry representing a discovered or configured Diameter peer server.

dbpAppAdvFromPeerVendorId.name: dbpAppAdvFromPeerVendorId
dbpAppAdvFromPeerVendorId.description: The IANA Enterprise Code value assigned to the vendor of the Diameter application.

dbpAppAdvFromPeerIndex.name: dbpAppAdvFromPeerIndex
dbpAppAdvFromPeerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the applications advertised as supported from each Diameter peer.

dbpAppAdvFromPeerType.name: dbpAppAdvFromPeerType
dbpAppAdvFromPeerType.description: The type of services supported for each application, accounting, authentication or both. acct(1) - accounting auth(2) - authentication both(3) - both accounting and authentication.

dbpPeerVendorTable.name: dbpPeerVendorTable
dbpPeerVendorTable.description: The table listing the Vendor IDs supported by the peer.

dbpPeerVendorEntry.name: dbpPeerVendorEntry
dbpPeerVendorEntry.description: A row entry representing a Vendor ID supported by the peer.

dbpPeerVendorIndex.name: dbpPeerVendorIndex
dbpPeerVendorIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the Vendor ID supported by the peer. Upon reload, dbpPeerVendorIndex values may be changed.

dbpPeerVendorId.name: dbpPeerVendorId
dbpPeerVendorId.description: The active vendor ID used for peer connections. diameterVendorIetf(0) -- IETF diameterVendor3gpp(10415) - 3GPP

dbpPeerVendorStorageType.name: dbpPeerVendorStorageType
dbpPeerVendorStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the objects are writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

dbpPeerVendorRowStatus.name: dbpPeerVendorRowStatus
dbpPeerVendorRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the dbpPeerVendorRowStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding dbpPeerVendorId has been set. Also, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding 'dbpPeerIndex' has been set. dbpPeerVendorId may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of dbpPeerVendorRowStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with dbpPeerVendorRowStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with dbpPeerVendorRowStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

dbpPerPeerStatsTable.name: dbpPerPeerStatsTable
dbpPerPeerStatsTable.description: The table listing the Diameter peer statistics.

dbpPerPeerStatsEntry.name: dbpPerPeerStatsEntry
dbpPerPeerStatsEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsState.name: dbpPerPeerStatsState
dbpPerPeerStatsState.description: Connection state in the Peer State Machine of the peer with which this Diameter server is communicating. closed - Connection closed with this peer. waitConnAck - Waiting for an acknowledgment from this peer. waitICea - Waiting for a Capabilities-Exchange- Answer from this peer. elect - When the peer and the server are both trying to bring up a connection with each other at the same time. An election process begins which determines which socket remains open. waitReturns - Waiting for election returns. r-open - Responder transport connection is used for communication. i-open - Initiator transport connection is used for communication. closing - Actively closing and doing cleanup.

dbpPerPeerStatsLastDiscCause.name: dbpPerPeerStatsLastDiscCause
dbpPerPeerStatsLastDiscCause.description: The last cause for a peers disconnection. rebooting - A scheduled reboot is imminent. busy - The peer's internal resources are constrained, and it has determined that the transport connection needs to be shutdown. doNotWantToTalk - The peer has determined that it does not see a need for the transport connection to exist, since it does not expect any messages to be exchanged in the foreseeable future. electionLost - The peer has determined that it has lost the election process and has therefore disconnected the transport connection.

dbpPerPeerStatsWhoInitDisconnect.name: dbpPerPeerStatsWhoInitDisconnect
dbpPerPeerStatsWhoInitDisconnect.description: Did the host or peer initiate the disconnect? host - If this server initiated the disconnect. peer - If the peer with which this server was connected initiated the disconnect.

dbpPerPeerStatsDWCurrentStatus.name: dbpPerPeerStatsDWCurrentStatus
dbpPerPeerStatsDWCurrentStatus.description: okay - Indicates the connection is presumed working. suspect - Indicates the connection is possibly congested or down. down - The peer is no longer reachable, causing the transport connection to be shutdown. reopen - Three watchdog messages are exchanged with accepted round trip times, and the connection to the peer is considered stabilized.

dbpPerPeerStatsTimeoutConnAtmpts.name: dbpPerPeerStatsTimeoutConnAtmpts
dbpPerPeerStatsTimeoutConnAtmpts.description: If there is no transport connection with a peer, this is the number of times the server attempts to connect to that peer. This is reset on disconnection.

dbpPerPeerStatsASRsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsASRsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsASRsIn.description: Abort-Session-Request messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsASRsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsASRsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsASRsOut.description: Abort-Session-Request messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsASAsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsASAsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsASAsIn.description: Number of Abort-Session-Answer messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsASAsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsASAsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsASAsOut.description: Number of Abort-Session-Answer messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsACRsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsACRsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsACRsIn.description: Number of Accounting-Request messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsACRsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsACRsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsACRsOut.description: Number of Accounting-Request messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsACAsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsACAsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsACAsIn.description: Number of Accounting-Answer messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsACAsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsACAsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsACAsOut.description: Number of Accounting-Answer messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsCERsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsCERsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsCERsIn.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Request messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsCERsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsCERsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsCERsOut.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Request messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsCEAsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsCEAsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsCEAsIn.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Answer messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsCEAsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsCEAsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsCEAsOut.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Answer messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsDWRsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsDWRsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsDWRsIn.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Request messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsDWRsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsDWRsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsDWRsOut.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Request messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsDWAsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsDWAsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsDWAsIn.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Answer messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsDWAsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsDWAsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsDWAsOut.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Answer messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsSTRsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsSTRsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsSTRsIn.description: Number of Session-Termination-Request messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsSTRsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsSTRsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsSTRsOut.description: Number of Session-Termination-Request messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsSTAsIn.name: dbpPerPeerStatsSTAsIn
dbpPerPeerStatsSTAsIn.description: Number of Session-Termination-Answer messages received from the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsSTAsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsSTAsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsSTAsOut.description: Number of Session-Termination-Answer messages sent to the peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsDWReqTimer.name: dbpPerPeerStatsDWReqTimer
dbpPerPeerStatsDWReqTimer.description: Device-Watchdog Request Timer, which is the interval between packets sent to peers.

dbpPerPeerStatsRedirectEvents.name: dbpPerPeerStatsRedirectEvents
dbpPerPeerStatsRedirectEvents.description: Redirect Event count, which is the number of redirects sent from a peer.

dbpPerPeerStatsAccDupRequests.name: dbpPerPeerStatsAccDupRequests
dbpPerPeerStatsAccDupRequests.description: The number of duplicate Diameter Accounting-Request packets received.

dbpPerPeerStatsMalformedReqsts.name: dbpPerPeerStatsMalformedReqsts
dbpPerPeerStatsMalformedReqsts.description: The number of malformed Diameter packets received.

dbpPerPeerStatsAccsNotRecorded.name: dbpPerPeerStatsAccsNotRecorded
dbpPerPeerStatsAccsNotRecorded.description: The number of Diameter Accounting-Request packets which were received and responded to but not recorded.

dbpPerPeerStatsAccRetrans.name: dbpPerPeerStatsAccRetrans
dbpPerPeerStatsAccRetrans.description: The number of Diameter Accounting-Request packets retransmitted to this Diameter server.

dbpPerPeerStatsTotalRetrans.name: dbpPerPeerStatsTotalRetrans
dbpPerPeerStatsTotalRetrans.description: The number of Diameter packets retransmitted to this Diameter server, not to include Diameter Accounting-Request packets retransmitted.

dbpPerPeerStatsAccPendReqstsOut.name: dbpPerPeerStatsAccPendReqstsOut
dbpPerPeerStatsAccPendReqstsOut.description: The number of Diameter Accounting-Request packets sent to this peer that have not yet timed out or received a response. This variable is incremented when an Accounting-Request is sent to this server and decremented due to receipt of an Accounting-Response, a timeout or a retransmission.

dbpPerPeerStatsAccReqstsDropped.name: dbpPerPeerStatsAccReqstsDropped
dbpPerPeerStatsAccReqstsDropped.description: The number of Accounting-Requests to this server that have been dropped.

dbpPerPeerStatsHByHDropMessages.name: dbpPerPeerStatsHByHDropMessages
dbpPerPeerStatsHByHDropMessages.description: An answer message that is received with an unknown Hop-by-Hop Identifier. Does not include Accounting Requests dropped.

dbpPerPeerStatsEToEDupMessages.name: dbpPerPeerStatsEToEDupMessages
dbpPerPeerStatsEToEDupMessages.description: Duplicate answer messages that are to be locally consumed. Does not include duplicate Accounting Requests received.

dbpPerPeerStatsUnknownTypes.name: dbpPerPeerStatsUnknownTypes
dbpPerPeerStatsUnknownTypes.description: The number of Diameter packets of unknown type which were received.

dbpPerPeerStatsProtocolErrors.name: dbpPerPeerStatsProtocolErrors
dbpPerPeerStatsProtocolErrors.description: Number of protocol errors returned to peer, but not including redirects.

dbpPerPeerStatsPermanentFailures.name: dbpPerPeerStatsPermanentFailures
dbpPerPeerStatsPermanentFailures.description: Number of permanent failures returned to peer.

dbpRealmMessageRouteTable.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteTable
dbpRealmMessageRouteTable.description: The table listing the Diameter Realm-based Message Route information.

dbpRealmMessageRouteEntry.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteEntry
dbpRealmMessageRouteEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter Realm Based Message Route server.

dbpRealmMessageRouteIndex.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteIndex
dbpRealmMessageRouteIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each Realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteApp.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteApp
dbpRealmMessageRouteApp.description: Application id used to route packets to this realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteType.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteType
dbpRealmMessageRouteType.description: The types of service supported for each realm application: accounting, authentication or both.

dbpRealmMessageRouteAction.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteAction
dbpRealmMessageRouteAction.description: The action is used to identify how a message should be treated based on the realm, application and type. local - Diameter messages that resolve to a route entry with the Local Action set to Local can be satisfied locally, and do not need to be routed to another server. relay - All Diameter messages that fall within this category MUST be routed to a next-hop server, without modifying any non-routing AVPs. proxy - All Diameter messages that fall within this category MUST be routed to a next-hop server. redirect - Diameter messages that fall within this category MUST have the identity of the home Diameter server(s) appended, and returned to the sender of the message.

dbpRealmMessageRouteACRsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteACRsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteACRsIn.description: Number of Accounting-Request messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteACRsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteACRsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteACRsOut.description: Number of Accounting-Request messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteACAsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteACAsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteACAsIn.description: Number of Accounting-Answer messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteACAsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteACAsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteACAsOut.description: Number of Accounting-Answer messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteRARsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteRARsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteRARsIn.description: Number of Re-Auth-Request messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteRARsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteRARsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteRARsOut.description: Number of Re-Auth-Request messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteRAAsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteRAAsIn

dbpRealmMessageRouteRAAsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteRAAsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteRAAsOut.description: Number of Re-Auth-Answer messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteSTRsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteSTRsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteSTRsIn.description: Number of Session-Termination-Request messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteSTRsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteSTRsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteSTRsOut.description: Number of Session-Termination-Request messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteSTAsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteSTAsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteSTAsIn.description: Number of Session-Termination-Answer messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteSTAsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteSTAsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteSTAsOut.description: Number of Session-Termination-Answer messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteASRsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteASRsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteASRsIn.description: Number of Abort-Session-Request messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteASRsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteASRsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteASRsOut.description: Number of Abort-Session-Request messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteASAsIn.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteASAsIn
dbpRealmMessageRouteASAsIn.description: Number of Abort-Session-Answer messages received from the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteASAsOut.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteASAsOut
dbpRealmMessageRouteASAsOut.description: Number of Abort-Session-Answer messages sent to the realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteAccRetrans.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteAccRetrans
dbpRealmMessageRouteAccRetrans.description: The number of Diameter accounting packets retransmitted to this realm.

dbpRealmMessageRouteAccDupReqsts.name: dbpRealmMessageRouteAccDupReqsts
dbpRealmMessageRouteAccDupReqsts.description: The number of duplicate Diameter accounting packets sent to this realm.

dbpRealmKnownPeersChosen.description: How the realm chooses which peer to send packets to. roundRobin - The peer used for each transaction is selected based on the order in which peers are configured. loadBalance - The peer used for each transaction is based on the load metric (maybe implementation dependent) of all peers defined for the realm, with the least loaded server selected first. firstPreferred - The first defined server is always used for transactions unless failover occurs. mostRecentFirst - The most recently used server is used first for each transaction.
